			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Chris Dombrowski</span></strong> is the author of a book of poems titled <em>By Cold Water</em> (Wayne State University Press), and his nonfiction has been published or is forthcoming in <em>Orion</em> and <em>Outside</em>. He lives with his family near Rattlesnake Creek in Missoula, Montana, where whitetail deer often drink from their plastic kiddie pool and a doe ate pizza off their picnic table.</p><a href="/contributors/chris-dombrowski" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
