		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>In a hyperbolical culture where a hamburger can be described as &ldquo;perfect&rdquo; or &ldquo;awesome,&rdquo; Chris Dombrowski&rsquo;s magical memoir &ldquo;<a href="/article/4484">The Oar: A Summer in Three Acts</a>&rdquo; [December 2010] reminded me of the true meaning of those words. His embrace of the world is awesome, his language as close to perfect as can be.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Ken Klonsky<br>Vancouver, British Columbia<br />Canada</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

